        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 7 at 11:43PM CDT until June 8 at 12:30AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>SVRSHV

The National Weather Service in Shreveport has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Little River County in southwestern Arkansas...
Central Hempstead County in southwestern Arkansas...
Northern Miller County in southwestern Arkansas...
Southeastern Sevier County in southwestern Arkansas...
Southeastern Howard County in southwestern Arkansas...
East central Bowie County in northeastern Texas...

* Until 1230 AM CDT.

* At 1142 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Wilton, or
near Ashdown, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Texarkana, Hope, Ashdown, Wilton, Tollette, Fulton, Washington,
Ogden, Ben Lomond, Saratoga, Mandeville, Genoa, Richmond, McNab,
Oakhaven, Bright Star, Hervey, Millwood, Homan, and Browntown.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
